
---


@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

' Main Classes
class SmartHome {
    +String physicalAddress
    +List<Room> rooms
    +List<Device> devices
    +List<ActivityLogEntry> activityLog
    +List<AutomationRule> automationRules
}

class Room {
    +String name
    +List<Device> devices
}

class Device {
    +String deviceId
    +String type
    +boolean isActive
    +String location
}

class SensorDevice {
    +String deviceId
    +String type
    +String location
    +List<SensorReading> readings
}

class ActuatorDevice {
    +String deviceId
    +String type
    +String location
    +List<ControlCommand> commands
}

class ActivityLogEntry {
    +Timestamp timestamp
    +String deviceID
    +String type (Sensor/Actuator)
    +String value
    +String status
}

class AutomationRule {
    +String ruleID
    +String description
    +boolean isActive
    +String precondition
    +List<ControlCommand> actionCommands
    +List<AutomationRule> dependentRules
    +List<AutomationRule> conflictingRules
}

class SensorReading {
    +Timestamp timestamp
    +String deviceID
    +double value
}

class ControlCommand {
    +Timestamp timestamp
    +String deviceID
    +String commandType
    +String status
}

' Relationships
SmartHome "1" -- "0..*" Room : contains
SmartHome "1" -- "0..*" Device : has
Room "1" -- "0..*" Device : contains
Device "--" SensorDevice : is-a
Device "--" ActuatorDevice : is-a
SmartHome "1" -- "0..*" ActivityLogEntry : logs
SmartHome "1" -- "0..*" AutomationRule : has
AutomationRule "1" -- "0..*" AutomationRule : dependsOn
AutomationRule "1" -- "0..*" AutomationRule : conflictsWith
SensorDevice "1" -- "0..*" SensorReading : generates
ActuatorDevice "1" -- "0..*" ControlCommand : sends

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:
- **SmartHome** manages rooms, devices, activity logs, and automation rules.
- **Room** can contain multiple **Devices** (either **SensorDevice** or **ActuatorDevice**).
- **Device** is an abstract class that subclasses into **SensorDevice** and **ActuatorDevice**.
- **SensorDevice** generates **SensorReading**, while **ActuatorDevice** sends **ControlCommand**.
- **ActivityLogEntry** records both sensor data and control commands with timestamps and statuses.
- **AutomationRule** defines conditions (precondition) and actions (control commands), and can have dependencies or conflicts with other rules.
- All entities are linked to **SmartHome** through its infrastructure map and log system.

